result: Biofuels are renewable energy sources derived from organic materials such as plants or animals. The first generation biofuels are produced from soybeans, corn and sugarcane and their production occurs through fermentation. Second-generation biofuels, also known as "grass gasoline", are those produced from wood waste (sawdust, for example), corn stalks, wheat straw or rapid growth grass and if They present as an alternative to the problems faced by the first generation, as the raw materials are cheap and abundant.
